    <h1>
        <u> Introduction</u> 
    </h1>
<p>The Bachelor of Technology (B.Tech) course curriculum is a comprehensive, <b>four-year (eight-semester) undergraduate engineering program</b> designed to blend scientific theory with practical application to train students for professional careers in technology and engineering.

It is structured <b>to provide a strong foundation in core sciences and mathematics (symbols used in mathematics are: &gt; , &lt; , &le; , &deg; , &#8377; , &ge; , &divide; , &sum; , &radic; , &infin;)</b> before transitioning to specialized engineering subjects, laboratory work, and professional development. </p>
<h2> 
    <u>Semester 1 Subjects</u>
 </h2>
<ol>
    <li>Fundamentals of Linear Algebra and Statistics</li>
    <li>Design Thinking</li>
    <li>Basic of Mechanical & Automation Engg. </li>
    <li>Soft Skills</li>
    <li>Data Structure</li>
    <li>Basic of Electronics engg.</li>
</ol>
